&lt;p&gt;The Business Development Manager applies healthcare industry knowledge, advanced sales acumen, and disciplined territory management to drive growth within an assigned geographic region or book of business. This role independently manages the full sales lifecycle from prospecting through close while maintaining rigorous pipeline management and consistent use of sales operations processes. The Business Development Manager builds influence with both customer stakeholders and internal partners through exceptional communication, consultative selling, and data-driven insights.&lt;/p&gt;
